def reverse_in_place(arr):
    left = 0
    right = len(arr) - 1
    
    while left < right:
        # Swap elements
        arr[left], arr[right] = arr[right], arr[left]
        # Move pointers toward the center
        left += 1
        right -= 1
    return arr

def find_missing_number(nums):
    n = len(nums)
    # Expected sum of range [0, n]
    expected_sum = n * (n + 1) // 2
    # Actual sum of the given array
    actual_sum = sum(nums)
    
    return expected_sum - actual_sum

# Example
nums = [3, 0, 1]
print(find_missing_number(nums))  # Output: 2

def reverse_array(arr):
    left = 0
    right = len(arr) - 1
    
    while left < right:
        # Swap elements
        arr[left], arr[right] = arr[right], arr[left]
        # Move pointers
        left += 1
        right -= 1
    return arr

# Example usage
input_arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
print(reverse_array(input_arr)) # Output: [5, 4, 3, 2, 1]

    "import wfdb\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.signal import butter, filtfilt\n",
    "import os"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "3be7fd62",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def bandpass_filter(signal, fs, lowcut=0.5, highcut=45, order=4):\n",
    "    nyq = 0.5 * fs\n",
    "    low = lowcut / nyq\n",
    "    high = highcut / nyq\n",
    "    b, a = butter(order, [low, high], btype='band')\n",
    "    return filtfilt(b, a, signal)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "013da21d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def normalize(signal):\n",
    "    return (signal - np.mean(signal)) / np.std(signal)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "6f56364e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def ptbxl_signal_to_image(record_path, save_path):\n",
    "    # Load ECG record\n",
    "    record = wfdb.rdrecord(record_path)\n",
    "    ecg = record.p_signal\n",
    "    fs = record.fs\n",
    "\n",
    "    lead_names = record.sig_name  # Lead labels\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Create figure with 12 subplots (6 rows × 2 columns)\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(6, 2, figsize=(12, 10))\n",
    "    axes = axes.flatten()\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in range(12):\n",
    "        signal = ecg[:, i]\n",
    "        signal = bandpass_filter(signal, fs)\n",
    "        signal = normalize(signal)\n",
    "\n",
    "        axes[i].plot(signal, linewidth=1)\n",
    "        axes[i].set_title(lead_names[i], fontsize=9)\n",
    "        axes[i].axis(\"off\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches=\"tight\", pad_inches=0)\n",
    "    plt.close()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "6c49c818",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "12-lead ECG image saved successfully!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "record_path = r\"C:\\Users\\nithi\\FinalYearProject\\Dataset\\PTB\\records500\\00000\\00001_hr\"\n",
    "output_dir = \"ecg_images\"\n",
    "os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "save_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"00000_lr.png\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ptbxl_signal_to_image(record_path, save_path)\n",
    "print(\"12-lead ECG image saved successfully!\")"

   "source": [
    "def bandpass_filter(signal, fs, lowcut=0.5, highcut=45, order=4):\n",
    "    nyq = 0.5 * fs\n",
    "    low = lowcut / nyq\n",
    "    high = highcut / nyq\n",
    "    b, a = butter(order, [low, high], btype='band')\n",
    "    return filtfilt(b, a, signal)"
   ]

    "    return (signal - np.mean(signal)) / np.std(signal)"
